.sp

.sp

.I val (lsr) 
: 
.B int -> int -> int
.sp

.B n lsr m
shifts 
.B n
to the right by 
.B m
bits\&.
This is a logical shift: zeroes are inserted regardless of
the sign of 
.B n
\&.
The result is unspecified if 
.B m < 0
or 
.B m >= bitsize
\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val (asr) 
: 
.B int -> int -> int
.sp

.B n asr m
shifts 
.B n
to the right by 
.B m
bits\&.
This is an arithmetic shift: the sign bit of 
.B n
is replicated\&.
The result is unspecified if 
.B m < 0
or 
.B m >= bitsize
\&.
.sp

